1
00:02:40,166 --> 00:02:42,416
[MAN 1A]
Hit us with that special move!

2
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,916
Aw, yeah, smooth stuff, buddy.

3
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,666
Woohoo!

4
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,875
[MISCREANTS chattering]

5
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:50,166
Let's see some footwork.

6
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:51,583
Nice. Keep it up!

7
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:56,625
[overlapping chatter continues]

8
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:15,916
[MAN 1D]
Hey, speakin' of beer...

9
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,791
You haven't drank
it all yet, have you?

10
00:03:17,875 --> 00:03:19,166
[MAN 1B]
I might'a.

11
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:20,833
Why don't you take
a look and see?

12
00:03:20,916 --> 00:03:23,250
[MISCREANTS chattering]

13
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:33,666
[DANCER 1A gasping]

14
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,083
It's a monster!

15
00:03:35,166 --> 00:03:38,125
[screams]

16
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:41,458
[MISCREANTS screaming]

17
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:05,083
[VOICE 1A chuckles]
You went too far, Sonia.

18
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:06,250
[VOICE 1B]
Thought you were smart.

19
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,208
Insubordination's no joke.

20
00:04:08,291 --> 00:04:10,208
[VOICE 1C] Getting transferred
to the Outside is basically

21
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:11,541
a death sentence.

22
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,916
[VOICE 1D] Sorry, but
you'll never make it back.

23
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,541
You won't last five
seconds out there

24
00:04:15,625 --> 00:04:17,041
with an attitude like yours.

25
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:35,666
[MAN 1G]
Who, that guy?

26
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,041
Nah, he didn't stand a chance.

27
00:04:37,125 --> 00:04:38,500
[WOMAN 1A]
Well, let's talk prices.

28
00:04:38,583 --> 00:04:39,791
You're working men, and--

29
00:04:49,166 --> 00:04:50,166
[SONIA gasps]

30
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:54,583
[WOMAN 1B crying]

31
00:04:54,666 --> 00:04:56,083
You okay? What happened?

32
00:04:56,166 --> 00:04:57,791
[WOMAN 1B]
He robbed me. Please help.

33
00:04:57,875 --> 00:04:59,250
You'll be all right.

34
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:02,375
Was it a red handbag
he took from you?

35
00:05:02,458 --> 00:05:03,500
Stay here!

36
00:05:04,875 --> 00:05:06,250
This is Officer Summers.

37
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:08,375
There's been a robbery
on 23rd Street!

38
00:05:08,458 --> 00:05:09,916
The victim wasn't
seriously injured,

39
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,166
so I'm leaving her and
pursuing the suspect.

40
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:14,250
Please send backup
as soon as you're able!

41
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:17,625
[ROBBER 1A grunts]

42
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:32,083
[SONIA gasps]

43
00:05:58,833 --> 00:06:00,166
Have a death wish?

44
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:03,708
But...

45
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:09,541
[SONIA]
Wait!

46
00:06:27,708 --> 00:06:29,333
[BEM]
It isn't holding back tonight.

47
00:06:43,708 --> 00:06:47,625
[POLICE chattering]
He hasn't been dead for long.

48
00:06:47,708 --> 00:06:51,416
[BYSTANDERS whispering]

49
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:52,500
[JANSEN sighs]

50
00:07:04,083 --> 00:07:05,000
[JANSEN sighs]

51
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:06,583
[WOODS]
You're late, Jansen.

52
00:07:07,958 --> 00:07:10,458
Would it have killed you
to finish that thing outside?

53
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:12,625
Oh, right. Forgot you cared.

54
00:07:12,708 --> 00:07:15,500
Summers? Certainly hope
you aren't a smoker.

55
00:07:15,583 --> 00:07:16,458
He hates the smell.

56
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:17,875
[SONIA]
Uh...

57
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:19,750
I take it you're the girl
scout who got transferred?

58
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:22,250
I'm Officer Sonia Summers.

59
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,250
[JANSEN]
This your first time Outside?

60
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:25,208
Yes.

61
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:26,333
[JANSEN]
Thought so.

62
00:07:26,416 --> 00:07:29,583
You've got that
Upper Town air to you.

63
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:31,708
So you were first
on the scene, right?

64
00:07:31,791 --> 00:07:33,875
Right. I witnessed
a robbery and th--

65
00:07:33,958 --> 00:07:34,916
[JANSEN]
Damn.

66
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,416
Why's it always
in our jurisdiction?

67
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:37,750
[SONIA]
Huh?

68
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,583
[JANSEN] Sixth victim
we've found this evening.

69
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:41,250
[WOODS] Been an average
of four killings a night

70
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,291
for the past two weeks.

71
00:07:43,375 --> 00:07:47,875
All of them drownings,
in places with no water source.

72
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:49,833
[SONIA] I never heard
about this back in Upper.

73
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:51,416
[JANSEN]
Of course you didn't.

74
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:54,083
Once you cross that bridge it's
like you're in another country.

75
00:07:54,166 --> 00:07:56,083
Why would this
case matter there?

76
00:07:56,166 --> 00:07:57,833
It's a serial killer.

77
00:07:59,875 --> 00:08:02,291
Give this purse back
to the owner, would ya?

78
00:08:02,375 --> 00:08:04,375
We put all the money back in.

79
00:08:04,458 --> 00:08:06,166
Isn't this evidence?

80
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:08,500
Shouldn't we take
some statements?

81
00:08:08,583 --> 00:08:11,083
[JANSEN] Your assignment
starts with us tomorrow.

82
00:08:11,166 --> 00:08:12,416
Get some rest.

83
00:08:17,541 --> 00:08:19,083
[HOMELESS MAN 1A] You're the
girl who left her car here,

84
00:08:19,166 --> 00:08:19,958
aren't ya?

85
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:21,291
[SONIA]
Yeah.

86
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:22,958
[HOMELESS MAN 1A] Sorry,
but an old lady came along

87
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:24,083
and sold it off.

88
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:25,125
[SONIA]
Huh?

89
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:28,750
[phone ringing]

90
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,000
[SONIA]
Hey, Mom.

91
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:33,875
Yeah, I know, it's late.
I just got to my room.

92
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:36,500
Yeah. Luckily it was furnished.

93
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:37,708
I'm fine.

94
00:08:37,791 --> 00:08:40,083
Don't worry so much.

95
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:41,791
I can make do on my own.

96
00:08:51,041 --> 00:08:52,708
[JANSEN]
Welcome to your new home.

97
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,083
You're with me today.

98
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:56,291
I'll teach you what ya need
to know to make it here.

99
00:09:03,916 --> 00:09:06,041
[JANSEN]
Rule number one in this town.

100
00:09:06,125 --> 00:09:08,333
Ya gotta be resourceful.

101
00:09:08,416 --> 00:09:10,541
--[WOMAN 1C] Yes.
--[CLERK 1A] And what else?

102
00:09:10,625 --> 00:09:11,916
[BOYS laughing]

103
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,708
[JANSEN]
What some might call "shady"

104
00:09:14,791 --> 00:09:16,666
others call "laid back."

105
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:33,375
Hold on, this is nowhere
near the crime sc--

106
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:34,541
[JANSEN]
Just wait a minute.

107
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:54,250
Cigars? Don't you hate smoke?

108
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:02,375
[JANSEN] You've heard
of the Helmsmen, right?

109
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:04,583
They run things
around this block.

110
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:06,833
As long as we're paid,
we stay out of it.

111
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:10,833
[SONIA]
What exactly are you saying?

112
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:12,875
In the Outside, the
Police and the Helmsmen

113
00:10:12,958 --> 00:10:14,708
look after one another.

114
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:16,916
Citizens are well aware,
and the smart ones

115
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,375
make use of us both.

116
00:10:18,458 --> 00:10:20,958
That's just how things
are done here, you get it?

117
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:22,833
Sounds like blatant
corruption to me.

118
00:10:22,916 --> 00:10:24,125
Easy, Girl Scout.

119
00:10:24,208 --> 00:10:25,583
We got three more stops.

120
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:29,958
Stop the car!

121
00:10:30,041 --> 00:10:32,000
We're in a rush.

122
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,041
Hey!

123
00:10:34,541 --> 00:10:36,458
[JANSEN]
Summers! Wait!

124
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:37,458
[SONIA]
Hold it!

125
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:38,666
--[TEEN 1A] Shit!
--[TEEN 1C] Ow!

126
00:10:40,250 --> 00:10:42,750
[SONIA]
You okay? What happened?

127
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:44,125
[TEEN 1C]
It's nothing serious.

128
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,625
But you--

129
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:55,333
I don't care about how
things are done here.

130
00:10:55,416 --> 00:10:57,291
If I see something
that I know is wrong,

131
00:10:57,375 --> 00:10:59,291
I will call it out.

132
00:10:59,375 --> 00:11:01,375
I'll be damned
if I don't believe it.

133
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:02,916
That must be why they sent you.

134
00:11:09,791 --> 00:11:12,750
[WATERMAN breathing heavily]

135
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:23,375
[WATERMAN]
Kill...

136
00:11:23,458 --> 00:11:25,500
I want to kill...

137
00:11:40,208 --> 00:11:41,666
[PROSTITUTE 1A gasps]
What the--?!

138
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,416
No! No!

139
00:11:45,666 --> 00:11:49,333
[CROWD yelling]

140
00:11:50,666 --> 00:11:53,250
[CROWD yelling]

141
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:58,500
[WOMEN whimpering]

142
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:02,916
[WATERMAN laughing]

143
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,958
So much fun!

144
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:08,000
[laughing continues]

145
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,958
[WATERMAN]
Wait. Why are you still alive?

146
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:37,291
[WATERMAN growls]

147
00:12:42,625 --> 00:12:43,791
[WATERMAN growls]

148
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,625
[WATERMAN yelling]

149
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:53,083
[WATERMAN chuckles]

150
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:55,416
You can do some
interesting things, stranger.

151
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,791
Did you throw away
your humanity too?

152
00:12:57,875 --> 00:12:59,875
Personally, it's the
best choice I ever made.

153
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:02,458
See, I almost drowned once,
but as I was dying,

154
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:04,708
I realized that nothing's
stronger than water.

155
00:13:04,791 --> 00:13:06,458
So instead of
letting it kill me,

156
00:13:06,541 --> 00:13:08,708
I decided to become
water myself!

157
00:13:08,791 --> 00:13:12,416
Now I can do lots
of things humans can't!

158
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:15,083
This one is irredeemable.

159
00:13:15,166 --> 00:13:16,500
[WATERMAN]
With this new body,

160
00:13:16,583 --> 00:13:19,333
I can go to Upper Town
and do whatever I want!

161
00:13:19,416 --> 00:13:20,750
But enough about me.

162
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:23,333
Did you get your powers
from the professor too?

163
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:24,500
--[BEM] Who's that?
--[WATERMAN] Don't know him?

164
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:26,125
That's weird. Whatever.

165
00:13:26,208 --> 00:13:28,250
I've done too much chatting
and not enough murdering

166
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:30,708
the last few seconds,
and I'm blaming you!

167
00:13:35,041 --> 00:13:37,916
[WATERMAN yelling]

168
00:14:01,708 --> 00:14:02,916
[WATERMAN gasps]

169
00:14:04,708 --> 00:14:05,416
[WATERMAN]
Damn.

170
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,583
That jerk pisses me off.

171
00:14:07,666 --> 00:14:09,958
I can't calm down
without killing.

172
00:14:10,041 --> 00:14:12,083
He ruined my fun!

173
00:14:21,375 --> 00:14:23,333
[BELO]
That guy seemed pretty strong.

174
00:14:23,416 --> 00:14:24,500
He'll survive.

175
00:14:24,583 --> 00:14:25,916
[BEM]
Belo.

176
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,375
[BELA] With how we're
fighting, to gain humanity.

177
00:14:28,458 --> 00:14:29,750
Bela.

178
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:32,791
[BELA] It's kinda funny that
this man threw his away.

179
00:14:32,875 --> 00:14:35,041
Then how good
can being human be?

180
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:36,125
--Just saying.
--[BELA] Sure.

181
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,583
You always talk like that.

182
00:14:37,666 --> 00:14:40,833
I don't want to become a
human like that water man.

183
00:14:40,916 --> 00:14:43,000
That thing's disgusting.

184
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:45,833
You think far too
highly of humans, Bela.

185
00:14:45,916 --> 00:14:48,583
And you think
far too little of them.

186
00:14:48,666 --> 00:14:50,458
So what should we do next?

187
00:14:50,541 --> 00:14:55,791
We must chase the scent of evil
before any more lives are lost.

188
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:57,291
So somber.

189
00:14:57,375 --> 00:15:00,375
[BEM] This corrupted man
is a threat to his species.

190
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:04,250
If we save enough humans,
then human is what we'll become.

191
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:08,375
[BELO]
Is that a fact or just a prayer?

192
00:15:10,916 --> 00:15:12,583
[OLD MAN 1A gurgling]

193
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:21,916
[WATERMAN laughing]

194
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,291
[MAN 1F gasps]

195
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:28,666
[WATERMAN grunts]

196
00:15:30,291 --> 00:15:33,375
Ugh. That shock is annoying!

197
00:15:33,458 --> 00:15:34,500
[grunts]

198
00:15:39,666 --> 00:15:40,625
[MAN 1F gasps]

199
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:43,000
[yells]

200
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:46,833
[JANSEN]
Hey, welcome back.

201
00:15:46,916 --> 00:15:48,250
[WOODS]
How'd it go?

202
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,708
The new girl was makin'
quite the face when she left.

203
00:15:50,791 --> 00:15:51,791
Huh?

204
00:15:54,958 --> 00:15:58,583
[WATERMAN grunting]

205
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,750
Professor!

206
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:03,208
[grunts]
Professor, please!

207
00:16:03,291 --> 00:16:05,708
I need you to make me stronger!

208
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:14,708
[WATERMAN yells]

209
00:16:25,666 --> 00:16:26,583
[WATERMAN growls]

210
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:28,375
What do you want?!

211
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:29,583
[grunts]

212
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:33,875
[WATERMAN grunts]

213
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:38,416
[WATERMAN grunts]

214
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,833
[WATERMAN growls]

215
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:46,458
This is all your fault!

216
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:49,000
Look at what you did
to me, you monster!

217
00:16:58,625 --> 00:16:59,750
[WATERMAN chuckles]

218
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:04,916
That same man...

219
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,791
[WATERMAN laughs]

220
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:08,041
Hi there!

221
00:17:08,125 --> 00:17:11,291
Welcome, Little Missy,
hope you enjoy the show!

222
00:17:13,416 --> 00:17:14,375
[SONIA grunts]

223
00:17:20,875 --> 00:17:21,875
[WATERMAN chuckles]

224
00:17:23,416 --> 00:17:24,750
Have a death wish?

225
00:17:35,541 --> 00:17:38,166
[WATERMAN chuckling]

226
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:43,291
[WATERMAN growls]

227
00:17:51,083 --> 00:17:52,041
[WATERMAN]
Ooh!

228
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:57,875
[WATERMAN]
Ah!

229
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:13,541
[WATERMAN laughing]

230
00:18:14,916 --> 00:18:15,875
[JANSEN]
Hey, Summers!

231
00:18:15,958 --> 00:18:17,708
Why the hell didn't
you contact me?

232
00:18:17,791 --> 00:18:19,291
[OFFICERS gasp]

233
00:18:19,375 --> 00:18:20,708
[JANSEN]
What is that?

234
00:18:22,875 --> 00:18:24,166
--[SONIA] Watch out!
--[WATERMAN yells]

235
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:57,833
[BEM (MONSTER) roars]

236
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,541
No... What are you?

237
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:05,916
This can't be real.

238
00:19:06,541 --> 00:19:10,625
[BEM (MONSTER) roars]

239
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:15,083
[WATERMAN grunting]

240
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:21,125
[WATERMAN grunts]

241
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:28,791
[WATERMAN yelling]

242
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:30,541
Why do this?!

243
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:33,791
You must know that you're
no different from me!

244
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:38,500
[WATERMAN yelling]

245
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:06,166
[BEM (MONSTER) growls]

246
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,291
You're a monster...

247
00:20:15,375 --> 00:20:17,583
See, Bem?
They're all the same.

248
00:20:28,125 --> 00:20:31,833
[SONIA screaming]

249
00:20:38,458 --> 00:20:39,583
[WOODS]
Summers, you here?

250
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:55,041
Seemed like you were hoping
you could trust that human.

251
00:20:55,125 --> 00:20:56,500
She's new to this town.

252
00:20:56,583 --> 00:20:59,041
It hasn't had time
to taint her as of yet.

253
00:20:59,125 --> 00:21:02,333
I wonder...
How many have betrayed us?

254
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,541
Thought we agreed
to stop counting.

255
00:21:04,625 --> 00:21:07,291
If we can't convince
ourselves to believe in humans,

256
00:21:07,375 --> 00:21:09,291
there's no way
we'll become them.

257
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:11,541
Bem's method is
the best we have.

